headline: This S&P 500 Stock Is Down 68%: Should You Buy It Now and Hold for 20 Years?
summary: This is the case with Nike (NYSE: NKE).  Nike's revenue has dipped on a year-over-year basis in four straight fiscal quarters.  Under previous CEO John Donahoe, Nike made some costly mistakes that it's still dealing with.
